
// This Hyperlambda code snippet concatenates a SQL query string by appending an "order by" clause and a "limit" clause to an existing SQL string. It uses [strings.concat] to join the current SQL string with additional ordering and limiting instructions, specifically ordering by "keyword_count" and "keyword_density" in descending order, and limiting the results to a specified number of records. The [set-value] slot updates the SQL string with this new concatenated value.
set-value:x:@.sql
   strings.concat:x:@.sql
      get-value:x:@.sql
      .:" order by keyword_count desc, keyword_density desc limit "
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/limit
